portfolioDeployed(string,address,address.details: Emitted when a Portfolio instance is deployed with createPortfolio method.

portfolioRegistered(string,address,addre.details: Emitted when a Portfolio instance is added to the Portfolios Registered array.

portfolioSupportAdded(string,address,add.details: Emitted when a Portfolio Support is added to the map of Portfolios Supported.

portfolioSupportDeleted(string,address,a.details: Emitted when a Portfolio Support is deleted from the map of Portfolios Supported.

portfolioUnregistered(address,address).details: Emitted when a Portfolio instance is removed from the Portfolios Registered array.

addPortfolioSupport(string,address).details: Add support of a Portfolio. Requirements: onlyOwner.

params.implementation_: creation byte code Hash of Portfolio contract to be added.

changeAdmin(address).details: Change Admin's address: authorized account to upgrade contract implementation.Requirements: onlyAdmin.

createPortfolio(string,address,string,st.details: Create a Portfolio instance (Beacon proxy) using the provided contractName and register it (Factory and Registry patterns). Requirements: whenNotPaused and portfolio byte code is supported.

params.contractName_: Name of Portfolio contract supported to be used to create a new instance of a portfolio.
params.owner_: Address of owner of portfolio - Transfer ownership of Portfolio created to owner_.
params.portfolioURI_: URI of Portfolio instance (Current Client implementation: IPFS CID of image file).

returns._0: address of created/deployed Portfolio Contract instance: BeaconProxy address.

delPortfolioSupport(string).details: Delete support of a Portfolio and emits event 'portfolioSupportDeleted' if successful.Requirements: onlyOwner.

params.contractName_: Name of Portfolio Contract to be deleted.

returns._0: boolean - False if Portfolio hash not in the list of supported Portfolios.

getAdmin().details: Returns Admin's address: authorized account to upgrade contract implementation.

getAllPortofliosRegistered().details: Get registered Portfolios' addresses (array). Requirements: whenNotPaused.

getBeaconPortoflioSupported(string).details: Get Beacon instance for a Portfolio supported.

getHashByteCode(bytes).details: Compute keccak256 Hash of bytecode provided.

params.byteCode_: creation byte code of Portfolio contract to be created.

getImplementation().details: Returns address of contract implementation: Implementation slot value (used by proxy to delegate calls).

initialize().details: Called after creation of contract dues to the requirements of a proxy-based upgradeability pattern: delegateCalls using proxy storage  - no contructor can be used

isPortoflioImplementationSupported(strin.details: Verify if Portfolio supported by checking the checking the name and implementation of Protfolio contract in the mapping '_portfoliosSupported'.

params.contractName_: Name of Portfolio Contract to be verified.

returns._0: boolean - False if Portfolio Name and Implementation not in the list of supported Portfolios.

isPortoflioRegistered(address).details: Verify if Portfolio rinstance egistred by checking the '_portfoliosRegisteredIndex'.

params.portfolioAddress: address of Portfolio instance to be verified.

returns._0: boolean - False if Portfolio instance not registered.

isPortoflioSupported(string).details: Verify if Portfolio supported by checking the name of Protfolio contract in the mapping '_portfoliosSupported'.

params.contractName_: Name of Portfolio Contract to be verified.

returns._0: boolean - False if Portfolio not in the list of supported Portfolios.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate that the this implementation remains valid after an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unregisterPortfolio(address).details: Unregister a Portfolio instance at address specified.Requirements: whenNotPaused and called by owner of Portfolio instance or Registry only.

params.portfolioAddress: address of Portfolio instance to be unregistered.

upgradePortfolioSupport(string,address).details: Upgrade implementation of Portfolio support: Beacon proxy pattern -> upgrade all instances using this beacon.

params.contractName_: Name of Portoflio support to upgrade.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

version().details: Returns Version of Registry contract (implementation version).
